{
  "analysis": "Background fastText training is running as PID 2581. The log shows it has started reading the data (11M words). We need to wait for completion, then verify `/app/work/model_raw.bin` is non-empty, evaluate accuracy on `/app/work/test.txt`, check size, and finally save a valid model to `/app/model.bin` under 150MB. I will poll with a bounded loop checking process liveness and model size, then inspect log and model files.",
  "plan": "Run a polling loop for up to about 5 minutes (10 iterations of 30 seconds) that checks whether PID 2581 is still alive and whether `model_raw.bin` exists with size > 0. After the loop, print the training log tail and list model files so we can decide whether to evaluate or continue waiting.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in $(seq 1 10); do\n  pid=$(cat /app/work/train.pid 2>/dev/null || true)\n  if [ -n \"$pid\" ] && [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then status=running; else status=finished; fi\n  size=$(stat -c %s /app/work/model_raw.bin 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  printf 'iter=%s status=%s bin_size=%s ' \"$i\" \"$status\" \"$size\"\n  echo \"[log tail]\"; tail -1 /app/work/train.log 2>/dev/null || true\n  if [ \"$status\" = finished ] && [ \"$size\" -gt 0 ]; then echo 'training_done_break'; break; fi\n  sleep 30\ndone\n",
      "duration": 65.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tail -30 /app/work/train.log 2>/dev/null || true\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /app/work/model_raw* 2>/dev/null || echo 'No model files'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
